integer constant overflowing the space allocated for it. You may need to use a larger type for the constant. A **signed int** holds a smaller value than an `unsigned int` because the **signed int** uses one bit to represent the sign.  \n  \n The following sample generates C4307:  \n  \n```  \n// C4307.cpp  \n// compile with: /W2  \nint i = 2000000000 + 2000000000;   // C4307  \nint j = (unsigned)2000000000 + 2000000000;   // OK  \n  \nint main()  \n{  \n}  \n```"}